{
  "texts": [
    "Graduate education must not only continue to emphasize research methods and scientific rigor but also emphasize and foster research evaluation skills.",
    "Universities would be wise to invest in shared AI infrastructure and interdisciplinary collaboration, enabling the training of large cohorts and fostering innovation across fields.",
    "AI tools are not authors and its use should be documented in the acknowledgement section (\"Tools Such as ChatGPT Threaten Transparent Science;",
    "Here Are Our Ground Rules for Their Use,\" 2023).",
    "The role of peer review, which has always had its share of issues (McCutchen, 1991) is transformed with the increase in use of free distribution and open-access archives that allows sharing of scholarly articles with peer review (arXiv.Org e-Print Archive, n.d.; bioRxiv.Org -the Preprint Server for Biology, n.d.; PsyArXiv Preprints, n.d.)."
  ]
}